Differentiate between JRE, JVM and JDK.
ans -
        Basically for devolving, running, Debugging a java program we need JDK. Means Java Developer kit.
        It need to be install on our system. Write now the version or JDK is 17 and 18(Beta Development).

        JDK has to part one is JRE means Java Runtime Environment and JVM means java visual Machine.

        So the basic differance between JDK, JRE and JVM is JDK is use to code executing java code. And its has
        some functionality of development the java source code.
        JRE is create the Environment for code execution.
        JVM is provide the implementation of JRE.